description:
The fight against Paradoxx suddenly comes to an end when the Rygulian, who had crashlanded on the planet after Zen had shot its spaceship, stabs Paradoxx from behind. Paradoxx releases Nira from his clutches and she lands on her head, apparently breaking her neck. The Rygulian gives Zen a few seconds time to get himself and Nira to safety. Zen gets back to his spaceship and prepares to seal the wormhole.

Noran, an intergalactic warlord, arrives at the wormhole. His scribe reveals himself to be an alternate Zen.

Backup story: The woman young Zen found was just a trick from a vine to lure its victims. He is freed from his trap by a mountain lion. Together, they get to the top of the mountain, where Zen begins his meditation.
name: Revelations

description:
Zen sets off a bomb which closes the wormhole, effectively defeating Paradoxx. The order in the universe is restored, which also means that Nira-X is alive again.

Backup story: Through meditation, Zen relives his birth. It is revealed that he is the result of an experiment to create a superior being. Deemed a failure, his 'father' orders his destruction. His 'mother' sents him off inside a launch tube, which lands on the planet Om years later.
name: Defining Alternity

volume.name: Zen Intergalactic Ninja: All-New Color Special

name: A Fire Upon The Earth!, Part II; The Crusade
A Fire Upon The Earth!, Part III; The Crusade, Part II
Battle Beyond the Ozone, Part I; The Crusade, Part III
Battle Beyond the Ozone, Part 2; The Crusade, Part IV

description: The alien race called Gordons discovered that Notan had targeted a planet for destruction. Trying to prevent this, they asked native Grok Bradok to enlist Zen's aid in helping them defeat Notan. Unknown to Zen that Grok was hired by the Gordons, Zen agreed to help.
name: Ominous

description: Zen discovers Grok was hired by the Gordons and is about to withdraw his offer to help, when Jade convinces him they are sincere in their plead for help. Zen asks Nira-X to join his band. Together they set out to Penflax-4, Grok's planet, where they come face-to-face with Notan.
name: Ominous, Part Two

description: Discovering her powers, Jade Bradok becomes the hero of the day when she absorbs the plasma energy Notan had drained from the planet, prevents Notan's plan of destroying her planet and saves the lives of her father Grok, Nira-X and Zen at the cost of her own life.
name: Ominous, Part Three

volume.name: Zen Intergalactic Ninja Summer Special: Video Warrior

description: Zen is on the planet Terania, when he is again contacted by Nira-X. Trying to leave the planet, Zen discovers he is wanted. However, it is Hunter Zen, an otherdimensional counterpart of Zen, who is wanted for multiple murders.
name: The Hunted, Part One

description: Zen and Nira-X try to fight Hunter Zen, who, thanks to enhancement drugs, is stronger and more durable than ever.

Hunter Zen uses too much energy to fight against Zen. Ultimately, Hunter Zen threatens to blow himself and Zen up. Nira-X suddenly arrives and punches Hunter Zen into a crater, where the bomb kills Hunter Zen. Zen is acquitted for the murders, which Hunter Zen committed and confessed before his death.

volume.name: Zen Intergalactic Ninja Tour of the Universe Special

description:
In the ultimate battle, Superman sacrificed his own life in order to defeat the rampaging alien, Doomsday. But now that the planet is saved, the world must deal with the loss of their greatest hero. Superman's closest allies, Batman, Wonder Woman, Aquaman, the Flash, and Green Lantern gather as they try to come to terms with the death of their friend. And as Clark Kent's fiance, Lois Lane, tries to cope with the loss of the man she loved, she discovers that Project Cadmus has stolen Superman's body and it is now up to her and Lex Luthor's girlfriend, Supergirl to stop them from cloning the Man of Steel.

Collects:
Adventured of Superman #498
Adventures of Superman #499
Adventures of Superman #500
Action Comics #685
Action Comics #686
Superman: The Legacy of Superman #1 (stories 1 and 4)
Superman the Man of Steel #20
Superman the Man of Steel #21
Superman #75 (selected material)
Superman #76
Superman #77
name: World Without A Superman

description: When an undercover cop is killed, apparently by a mob boss, the worlds of Nightwing and the Huntress collide in this trade paperback that collects the 4-issue NIGHTWING/HUNTRESS miniseries. As the two heroes approach the policeman's brutal murder from very different angles - Nightwing looking for justice and the truth, Huntress looking for vengeance - they find that opposites really do attract
name: Nightwing/Huntress

description: A new softcover collecting the blockbuster story "Absolute Power," originally presented in SUPERMAN/BATMAN #14-18! In this reality-bending tale, Superman and Batman rule Earth with an iron fist. Before long, the World's Finest Duo is sent careening through a series of bizarre alternate earths, facing an assortment of classic DC characters including Kamandi, Sgt. Rock, Haunted Tank, and many more!
name: Absolute Power

description: IAN CHURCHILL (Hulk, Supergirl) continues his brand new creator-owned series! Lieutenant Greene gets a tour of Ocean Point and ends up seeing more than expected! Meanwhile, in South Africa, Jake's life is accidentally put in mortal danger and only Marineman can possibly save him but at what cost?!
name: Deep Trouble

description:
Don't miss this explosive collection featuring SUPERMAN/BATMAN #20-25, the issues that reunited writer Jeph Loeb with the dynamic art team of Ed McGuinness and Dexter Vines!

Can the World's Finest pair take on a squad of revenge-seeking heroes who are on the hunt for the murderer of one of their teammates? Things are sure to heat up fast, because Batman and Superman are at the top of their suspect list!

And how do Darkseid, Lex Luthor, Superwoman and Batwoman fit into all of this? DC's two greatest icons go through the wringer and across multiple dimensions for an explosive finale that ties up many of the story elements started in SUPERMAN/BATMAN VOL. 1: PUBLIC ENEMIES.
name: Vengeance

description:
This explosive volume collects the best-selling SUPERMAN/BATMAN #28-33!

The JLA's Martian Manhunter attacks Batman! The villainous Parasite and Titano return! Superman's allegiances will be tested in this story involving the Green Lantern Corps and more!
name: Enemies Among Us
The Return of Orang, The Ape That is Human
Ebony's X-Ray Eyes

description: Tokyo burns with the genetic heat of the final light. Can Generation Hope tame it, or will the X-Men have to snuff it out? The first battle for the future of mutantkind comes to a climax, with Bio-titans fighting between the sky-scrapers when hope and despair come to blows. The first arc of the most-anticipated new book of 2010 concludes! Part 3 (of 3)
name: The Future is a Four-Letter Word, Part 3

description: Ellen Dolan returns Homer Creep's engagement ring.
name: Oriental Agents
The Kidnapping of Ebony
The Haunted House
Christmas Spirit of 1940: Black Henrey and Simple Simon
The Manly Art of Self Defense

description: Before their children, the Runaways, became their greatest nemeses, the villainous Pride of Los Angeles faced their greatest threat when a destitute and penniless Tony Stark came to Los Angeles. Through cat's-paws both super powered and mundane they tried to break him, but every attempt failed. But now they've made a mistake by kidnapping the person closest to him and sacrificing her to their dark masters, The Gibborim. Tony will do everything to get her back, including attacking The Pride on their own turf ... with some surprise guest-stars in tow!!!
name: Industrial Revolution Part 5: No Way Back
Capt. Marvel Jr. Battles Big Smokey

description: Its the return of your favorite furry flatfoots in an all-new original ongoing series! When all the furry denizens in the four corners of the globe turn feral, it's up to the world's most daring diminutive detectives to solve the mystery. But will there be dissension in the team when they learn that one of the Rangers hold a secret about Gadget's past that could unlock the entire case? Join DARKWING DUCK writer Ian Brill and MARVEL SUPERHERO SQUAD artist Leonel Castellani for part 2 of Worldwide Rescue, brought to you by BOOM! Studios and the Disney Afternoon Revolution!
name: Worldwide Rescue Part 2

description: These seminal tales from the 1960s, torn from the pages of SHOWCASE #8, THE FLASH #105, 106, 110, 113, 117, 122, 140 and 155, introduced the Scarlet Speedster's Rogues Gallery, including Captain Cold, Mirror Master, Gorilla Grodd, the Weather Wizard, Captain Boomerang and Heat Wave all prominently featured in FINAL CRISIS: ROGUES' REVENGE
name: The Flash vs The Rogues

description: Out of the great halls of Asgard, home of the Norse Gods, came one of the greatest Norse legends. Thor, powerful god of thunder, and his brother Loki, the trickster, were eager to resolve an argument: Does strength always win, or do brains always beat brawn? To find an answer, they travel to the strange and forbidding land of giants. There they will face a series of challenges that will prove once and for all which god is right. Or will it?

volume.name: Thor & Loki in the Land of Giants
